# Shopware 6.7 DDEV – Project Context (Template)

## Project
- **Base:** Shopware 6.7 e-commerce (this repo as a template for different projects).
- **Shopware version:** 6.7. Use official docs as reference.

## Development environment
- Use **DDEV** (do not assume local PHP/Composer outside DDEV).
- Common commands: `ddev start`, `ddev ssh`, `make ddev-storefront`, `make ddev-admin`, `make ddev-build`, `make ddev-cache`, `make ddev-import-db`, `make ddev-plugins`, `make ddev-theme`.
- Storefront URL per project: `https://<projectname>.ddev.site` (DDEV project name in `.ddev/config.yaml`).

## Documentation (always check)
- **Developer:** https://developer.shopware.com/
- **User/Docs:** https://docs.shopware.com/en
- **Frontends (Headless/Custom Storefronts):** https://developer.shopware.com/frontends/
- LLM-optimized docs: https://developer.shopware.com/llms.txt

## Context7 MCP (up-to-date docs)
- **Setup:** Add `CONTEXT7_API_KEY=your_key` to `.env.local` (gitignored) or `.env.ddev`; get a free key at [context7.com/dashboard](https://context7.com/dashboard). `.cursor/run-context7-mcp.sh` sources it so the key is not in mcp.json.
- **Verify:** From project root run `bash .cursor/run-context7-mcp.sh --check` — should print "OK: CONTEXT7_API_KEY is set". In Cursor: Settings → MCP → ensure "context7" is connected; in chat try e.g. "How do I add a CMS block in Shopware? use context7".
- Use in prompts: `use context7` or target a library: `use library /shopware/docs` (IDs below).
- **Shopware library IDs (Context7):**
  - `/shopware/shopware` – Shopware 6 platform (GitHub)
  - `/websites/shopware_en` – Shopware docs (docs.shopware.com/en)
  - `/shopware/docs` – Developer documentation
  - `/shopware/store-api-reference` – Store API reference
  - `/shopware/frontends` – Shopware Frontends (Vue/custom storefronts)
  - `/shopware/administration` – Administration (JS/Vue)
  - `/shopware/meteor` – Meteor design system

## Code & conventions
- Best practices, lean code. No unnecessary abstractions.
- Prefer existing dependencies; new ones only after discussion.
- Never hardcode credentials, tokens, or environment-specific values.
